    "what_description": "Dendrochilum schweinfurthianum is a species of orchid in the family Orchidaceae. It is native to the Philippines. This terrestrial orchid has a short rhizome, and its roots are cord-like and wiry. The stems are thin, erect, and usually 10-30 cm tall, with 2-3 linear to lanceolate leaves that are 5-15 cm long. The inflorescence is a raceme, usually 5-10 cm long, bearing 2-5 flowers that are white or pale yellow with a purple labellum.",
