    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Dendrochilum schweinfurthianum are its anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial activities, which make it useful in wound healing and infection prevention. The plant's flavonoids, including kaempferol and quercetin, are responsible for its antioxidant properties, which protect against cell damage and oxidative stress. Dendrochilum schweinfurthianum also exhibits antimalarial properties, with its sesquiterpenes and diterpenes contributing to the inhibition of Plasmodium falciparum growth. Additionally, the plant's saponins have been shown to possess immunomodulatory effects, modulating the immune response and potentially treating autoimmune diseases. The plant's essential oils, rich in monoterpenes and sesquiterpenes, exhibit antifungal and insecticidal activities, providing protection against fungal infections and pests.",
